SummaryEnglish: Based on the world-famous pop culture phenomenon, this 2D-animated series follows Baby Shark and his best friend William as they journey on fun-filled comedic adventures in their community of Carnivore Cove, make new friends and sing original catchy tunes along the way.

1.SummaryEnglish: The season’s hottest toy, Burpin’ Bubbz, is at the top of Baby and William’s Fishmas wish lists, and when Santa Jaws goes missing, it’s up to them to save the holiday.

12.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark and William show everything they love about Carnivore Cove.

13.SummaryEnglish: Baby and William are putting on a game show and viewers can play along.

1.SummaryEnglish: When Baby Shark loses his tooth for real, he and William team up with an unexpected ally to track it down.

2.SummaryEnglish: A game of Barnacle Ball turns into a rescue mission after Hank's pet rock, Rocky, is hit into the Lair of the Slobber Slug.

3.SummaryEnglish: When Baby Shark and friends enter a battle of the bands, Baby's rivalry with Shadow gets heated.

4.SummaryEnglish: Baby learns that when it comes to feeling better, there's no substitute to rest, covering your sneezes, and staying home

5.SummaryEnglish: Inspired by their favorite TV show, Baby Shark and William set out to be superheroes.

6.SummaryEnglish: Shadow teases William for being a scaredy-fish.

7.SummaryEnglish: After discovering a map to the Legendary Loot, the Shark family splits up to track down the treasure.

8.SummaryEnglish: Baby convinces Daddy to say yup to everything for one day.

9.TitleEnglish: When You Wish Upon a Fish
9.SummaryEnglish: Baby and friends set out to climb Wish Mountain and make a wish on the legendary shooting starfish, Ol' Sea Breeze.

10.SummaryEnglish: When Shadow tells Baby that he isn't a real shark because of his sweet nature, Baby agrees to a shark-off: a contest to prove who is the sharkiest; when they bite off more than they can chew, Baby must save the day by being himself.

11.SummaryEnglish: The fate of the city's squidapple supply lies in Baby's fins when he accidentally assumes the role of Mayor on a big day.

12.SummaryEnglish: The Sharks go on the family game show Sink or Swim and find they're in hot water with their competition, the Fishes.

13.SummaryEnglish: When Goldie's feeling down, Baby and friends decide to put on a musical to help her shine.

14.SummaryEnglish: When Grandma's shortcake goes missing before the bake-off, it's a case for Detective Baby Shark and William Watson.

15.SummaryEnglish: As Super Shark and Captain Kelp, Baby Shark and William set out to save playtime-but is Captain Kelp just a sidekick?

16.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark adopts a teensy tiny pet, but is he ready for a big responsibility?

17.SummaryEnglish: Jealous of Baby Shark's popularity, Shadow rebrands the Wreck as his own personal amusement park.

18.SummaryEnglish: When Baby Shark and friends are playing knights and royals, Vola wants to be more than just a princess.

19.SummaryEnglish: After a selfish fish takes over the putt-putt, Baby Shark and William must find a champion mini-golf player to defeat him.

20.SummaryEnglish: Hank struggles to overcome his fears without the help of his pet rock, Rocky.

21.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark faces his one big fear when he meets a ghostfish.

22.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark and William travel to the deep dark depths to try to retrieve Baby's lost microphone.

25.SummaryEnglish: Chucks tries to help Baby Shark and his friends win the annual Snowball Bonanza against Carnivore Cove's neighbouring town.

26.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark goes undercover to figure out the perfect gift for Mommy Shark.

27.SummaryEnglish: When a game of coral pins bowling gets out of hand, Baby must learn to control his shark strength

28.SummaryEnglish: when Bentley Barracuda threatens to evict Briny from the town square, Baby must try to make his voice heard.

29.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark's Barnacle Ball team hires an expert coach who uses unusual methods

30.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark bites off more than he can chew before his big dance party with Grandma Shark.

31.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark tries to give William the best Best Fin-ship Day ever.

32.SummaryEnglish: When Vola's skatefish board goes missing before a big event, Detective Baby Shark and William Watson are on the case.

37.SummaryEnglish: The Tentacools get caught up in the trappings of being rock starfishes.

38.SummaryEnglish: When Hank discovers his friends are going easy on him during dodge bubble, he sets out to become a tough fishy just like Shadow.

39.SummaryEnglish: As the kids get ready to celebrate Mother's Day, William starts to worry about why his family looks different than everybody else's.

40.SummaryEnglish: Baby enlists Goldie's help to show Penny Piranha how to stop biting.

41.SummaryEnglish: It’s a battle of the dads when Grandpa and Daddy can’t agree on the best way to camp.

42.SummaryEnglish: When Baby's new neighbor doesn’t like him, Baby pulls out all the stops to change his mind.

1.SummaryEnglish: Goldie blames her missing treats on a monster.

2.SummaryEnglish: Vigo's evil plot to turn every fishy into babies backfires when toddlers Super Shark and Captain Kelp turn out to be a finful.

3.SummaryEnglish: When all the friends decorate with their special thing, Hank is unsure what his special thing is.

4.SummaryEnglish: When a noisy water bug takes up residence in the Sharks' home, the family will do whatever it takes to reclaim the peace and quiet they lost.

5.SummaryEnglish: Chucks teaches Baby and William the joys of celebrating Hanukkah, the Fishtival of Lights.

6.SummaryEnglish: Goldie finds an ice-skating partner in the unlikeliest of fishies…Shadow?!

7.SummaryEnglish: The fishy friends find themselves locked out when they can't remember the secret password to get inside their clubhouse.

8.SummaryEnglish: The Sharks compete in a series of games to see which of them is the Monday Funday Chomp-ion.

9.SummaryEnglish: Baby and Teensy embrace their fancy side to win a dance contest for pets.

10.SummaryEnglish: When the owner of Iceberg Ice Cream, Scoops, has to rush out on a frosty emergency, he leaves Baby Shark and William in charge of his parlor.

11.SummaryEnglish: Vola puts it all on the line to win an epic game of Extreme Dodge Bubble.

12.SummaryEnglish: When Mommy loses her and Baby's tickets to the big Glow-J concert, they retrace her wake to track them down.

13.SummaryEnglish: When Finnegan Travelfins leaves Carnivore Cove out of his travel guide, Baby and William make a video to show off their town!

14.SummaryEnglish: Shadow's insincere apologies put a strain on his friendship with Bait and Switch.

15.SummaryEnglish: Baby struggles to let go of his lucky necklace when the time comes to pass it along to somefishy else.

16.SummaryEnglish: Super Shark and Captain Kelp spot Vigo doing errands around town and are convinced he's hatching a sinister plot.

17.SummaryEnglish: When Rayna asks William to be more responsible, he sets out to become a grownup fishy named Billiam.

18.SummaryEnglish: When Baby discovers Hank and Goldie aren't speaking to each other, he concocts an elaborate plan to bring them back together.

21.SummaryEnglish: When a group of bunny slugs wander off, Vola sets out to round them up all by herself.

22.SummaryEnglish: When William adopts a sea pig named Chumby, the little squirt is more trouble than William bargained for.

23.SummaryEnglish: Baby Shark helps Mommy find the perfect musical instrument to play in their family band.

24.SummaryEnglish: When a silly video of Daddy goes viral, he finds he doesn't want to be internet famous! Can Baby make another popular video?

25.SummaryEnglish: Baby, William, and Goldie help a Medieval Tides swordfish regain his confidence.

26.SummaryEnglish: When Mommy goes away for the weekend, the rest of the the family take a vacation from the rules.

27.SummaryEnglish: Vola, Goldie, Chucks, and Hank feel left out when they learn that Baby and William have been keeping a super secret.

28.SummaryEnglish: To prepare for their first big TV interview, Fishy Force trains to be just like their favorite comic book heroes.

29.SummaryEnglish: Fishy Force takes on a villain who steals all the treats in Carnivore Cove.

30.SummaryEnglish: When Costello quits, Vigo sets out to be a supervillain without his henchfishy.

31.SummaryEnglish: When Baby and his friends are asked to perform at a music festival, they can't decide which genre of song to play.

32.SummaryEnglish: Detective Baby Shark and William Watson solve a crabby mystery.

33.SummaryEnglish: When all the other fishies are out of town during winter vacation, Baby and William create their very own fin-credible day of friendship.

34.SummaryEnglish: Chucks takes a unique approach to camping on his first trip with the Fishy Scouts.

35.SummaryEnglish: When dancing is outlawed in Carnivore Cove, Baby Shark will do whatever it takes to get the town dancing again!

36.SummaryEnglish: Baby and William try to help Ernie make a best friend.

37.SummaryEnglish: When Baby gets his sweater dirty on Shark family picture day, he sets off to fix his mess.

38.SummaryEnglish: Penny and Wallace team up to perform in a two-fishy talent show.

39.SummaryEnglish: After injuring his fin, Hank is afraid to go to the doctor.

40.SummaryEnglish: Baby and William search high and low for the most delicious flownuts in the ocean.

41.SummaryEnglish: Hank becomes frustrated when he has to share his father's time with his new stepsisters.

42.SummaryEnglish: As everyfishy prepares for Smoothie Day, William makes a new friend whose jokes are more hurtful than funny.

43.SummaryEnglish: Baby and Grandpa team up to win a bubble rocket competition.

44.SummaryEnglish: Goldie puts on a play about a skatefish boarding legend and casts herself in the lead, instead of giving Vola a chance to shine.

45.SummaryEnglish: The Sharks help Wavey Jones search for his disco ball so he can throw a jaw-some party.

46.SummaryEnglish: When Hank accidentally takes an important treasure from Swimmy Hall, he goes on a sneaky mission to set things right.

47.SummaryEnglish: Baby gets carried away when he helps Grandma and Grandpa plan their vow renewal ceremony.

48.SummaryEnglish: Melanie Fontana Swimming Solo: Mommy Shark demonstrates a power that blows Baby away, sending him on a journey to find the same superpower within: Self-soothing!

49.SummaryEnglish: Instead of confronting his pals about a problem, Chucks decides to find a new friend group.

50.SummaryEnglish: When the Crystal Coral Tree goes missing, Detective Baby Shark and William Watson are on the case. Guests: Jim Rash and John Michael Higgins

51.SummaryEnglish: Goldie embraces her serious side to impress a director from Chomp City.

52.SummaryEnglish: Everyfishy wants to join Shadow’s cool new club.

1.SummaryEnglish: Lannie visits Carnivore Cove and joins Baby and his friends for a dance marathon.

2.SummaryEnglish: Baby is thrilled to have a new bubbaloon pal until he faces the possibility of losing it. Guest Star: Chloe Fineman

3.SummaryEnglish: When Goldie becomes a psychic, Baby and William set out to make her predictions come true.

4.SummaryEnglish: Baby and William look after a baby reef rabbit and learn how difficult it is to be a parent. Guest Star: John Michael Higgins

5.SummaryEnglish: Hank goes on a swashbuckling adventure to help Captain Bubblebeard recover his signature beard.

6.SummaryEnglish: When William becomes moody and distant during an epic sleepover, Detective Baby Shark sets out to learn why.

7.SummaryEnglish: The Sharks travel to a tropical resort where Baby makes a plan to have the perfect vacation.

8.SummaryEnglish: Grandpa loses the TV remote and searches high and low to find it.

34.SummaryEnglish: Chucks starts giving out Nicknames to everyfishy in Carnivore Cove, including Baby Shark. However, Baby Shark is given a nickname that he doesn't like.

35.SummaryEnglish: When Grandma loses her glasses, Baby becomes her guide for the day.

36.SummaryEnglish: It's up to Baby and William to save the Carnivore Cove Nautical Night Fair.
